      <item>
          <title>Everything Wrong with MSIX: The Virtual Filesystem Trap</title>
          <pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
          <author>Marc-André Moreau</author>
          <link>https://awakecoding.com/posts/everything-wrong-with-msix-the-virtual-filesystem-trap/</link>
          <guid>https://awakecoding.com/posts/everything-wrong-with-msix-the-virtual-filesystem-trap/</guid>
          <description>MSIX solves real packaging problems, but package identity and filesystem virtualization change where applications and settings live. For ISVs, the settings path is the bigger risk: customer state, rollback, support workflows, and migration from MSI all depend on predictable paths.</description>
          <bannerImage>https://awakecoding.com/images/banners/everything-wrong-with-msix-the-virtual-filesystem-trap.png</bannerImage><tags>
